Article 10: Members enjoy the following rights:  

(1) The right to vote, be elected, and make decisions in this organization; 

(2) The right to participate in the activities of this organization; 

(3) The right to have priority to the services of this organization (such as web pages, periodicals, conferences); 

(4) The right to criticize, make suggestions, and supervise the work of this organization; 

(5) The right to join and leave the organization voluntarily.  

Article 11: Members shall fulfill the following obligations:  

(1) Carry out the resolutions of this organization; 

(2) Protect the legitimate rights and interests of this organization; 

(3) Complete the work assigned by this organization; 

(4) Pay the membership fee as stipulated (to be determined separately); 

(5) Report to the organization and provide relevant materials;  

Article 12: Members who wish to withdraw from the organization should notify the organization in writing and return their membership card. If a member does not pay the membership fee or does not participate in the activities of the organization for a year, they are considered to have withdrawn automatically.  

Article 13: If a member seriously violates the rules of this organization, they may be expelled by a vote of the Board of Directors or the Executive Board.  

## Chapter 4: Organization Structure and Election/Removal of Responsible Persons  

Article 14: The highest authority of this group is the General Assembly (or Representative Assembly). The powers of the General Assembly (or Representative Assembly) are:  

1. To draft and amend the constitution; 

2. To elect and remove directors; 

3. To review the work report and financial report of the board of directors; 

4. To decide on termination matters; 

5. To decide on other significant matters.

