Article 27: The president of this group is the legal representative of the group, and is recommended by the competent authority. The legal representative of this group shall not concurrently serve as the legal representative of other groups.  

Article 28: The president of this group exercises the following powers:  

(1) To convene and preside over the board of directors (or standing committee); 

(2) To inspect the implementation of resolutions by the general assembly of members, the board of directors (or standing committee); 

(3) To represent this group in signing relevant important documents; 

(4) To guide and coordinate the work of the secretary-general and deputy secretary-general.  

Article 29: The secretary- general of this group exercises the following powers:  

(1) To preside over the daily work of the office, organize the implementation of the annual work plan; 

(2) To coordinate the work of various branches, representative offices, and substantive institutions; 

(3) To nominate the deputy secretary-general as well as the main person in charge of each office, branch, representative office, and substantive institution, for decision by the board of directors or standing committee; 

(4) To decide on the hiring of full-time staff of the office, representative offices, and substantive institutions; 

(5) To report to the president on major daily work involving academic activities, personnel, funds, etc; 

(6) To handle other daily affairs.  

## Chapter 5: Asset Management, Use Principles  

Article 30 The sources of funds for this organization are:  

(1) Membership fees; 

(2) Donations; 

(3) Government subsidies; 

(4) Income from activities or services carried out within the approved business scope; 

(5) Interest; 

(6) Other lawful income.  

Article 31 This organization collects membership fees in accordance with relevant national regulations.
